In pursuit of the greatest possible correlation with the performance of the RJ/CRB TOTAL RETURN INDX index, the MF will employ an indirect replication method, which means that it will enter into one or more OTC swap contracts enabling it to achieve its investment objective. These swap contracts will serve to exchange (i) the value of the MF’s

assets, which will consist of cash and/or balance sheet assets (excluding any securities received as collateral), for (ii) the value of the securities that underlie the RJ/CRB TOTAL RETURN INDX index.

The equities in the MF’s assets will notably be equities that make up the RJ/CRB TOTAL RETURN INDX index, as well as other international equities, from all economic sectors, listed on all markets, including the small capitalisation markets,
